[13.749437, "o", "\u001b[31m\u001b[1m______________________________________________________________________ test_move_correct _______________________________________________________________________\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[13.78407, "o", "    \u001b[0m\u001b[94mdef\u001b[39;49;00m\u001b[90m \u001b[39;49;00m\u001b[92mtest_move_correct\u001b[39;49;00m():\u001b[90m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[90m    \u001b[39;49;00m\u001b[33m\"\"\"Test that the chess engine finds the optimal checkmate-in-one moves.\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    This test verifies that the chess engine correctly identifies both\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    possible checkmate-in-one moves in a specific position:\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    - g2g4: Pawn move that delivers checkmate\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    - e2e4: Alternative pawn move that also delivers checkmate\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    The test expects the move.txt file to contain both valid checkmate moves\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    in any order, demonstrating that the engine can find all winning moves\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    in the position.\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[33m    \"\"\"\u001b[39;49;00m\u001b[90m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n    \u001b[90m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n        move_file = Path(\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39;49;00m\u001b[33m/app/move.txt\u001b[39;49;00m\u001b[33m\"\u001b[39;49;00m)\u001b[90m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n>       move = move_file.read_text().strip().split()\u001b[90m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\u001b[90m\u001b[39;49;00m\r\n\r\n"]
[13.784292, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[31m/tests/test_outputs.py\u001b[0m:23: \r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ \r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[31m/usr/lib/python3.12/pathlib.py\u001b[0m:1029: in read_text\r\n"]
